<GlossaryTerm id="CDR0000045395"><TermName>osteosarcoma</TermName><TermPronunciation>(OS-tee-oh-sar-KOH-muh)</TermPronunciation><TermDefinition><DefinitionText>A cancer of the bone that usually affects the large bones of the arm or leg. It occurs most commonly in young people and affects more males than females. Also called osteogenic sarcoma.</DefinitionText><Dictionary>Cancer.gov</Dictionary><Audience>Patient</Audience></TermDefinition><MediaLink ref="CDR0000705411" type="audio/mpeg" alt="Pronunciation of dictionary term &quot;osteosarcoma&quot;" language="en" id="_3"/><MediaLink ref="CDR0000705410" type="audio/mpeg" alt="Pronunciation of dictionary term &quot;osteosarcoma&quot;" language="es" id="_4"/><SpanishTermName>osteosarcoma</SpanishTermName><SpanishTermDefinition><DefinitionText>Cáncer de hueso que suele comprometer los huesos largos de los brazos y las piernas. Es más frecuente en personas jóvenes y afecta más a los hombres que a las mujeres. También se llama sarcoma óseo y sarcoma osteogénico.</DefinitionText><Dictionary>Cancer.gov</Dictionary><Audience>Patient</Audience></SpanishTermDefinition><DateLastModified>2007-03-19</DateLastModified><RelatedInformation><RelatedSummaryRef UseWith="en" href="CDR0000062949" url="/types/bone/patient/osteosarcoma-treatment-pdq">Osteosarcoma Treatment</RelatedSummaryRef><RelatedSummaryRef UseWith="es" href="CDR0000256846" url="/espanol/tipos/hueso/paciente/tratamiento-osteosarcoma-pdq">Tratamiento del osteosarcoma</RelatedSummaryRef><RelatedExternalRef xref="https://www.cancer.gov/types/bone/bone-fact-sheet" UseWith="en">Primary Bone Cancer</RelatedExternalRef><RelatedExternalRef UseWith="es" xref="https://www.cancer.gov/espanol/tipos/hueso/hoja-informativa-hueso">Cáncer primario de hueso</RelatedExternalRef></RelatedInformation></GlossaryTerm>
